{"title_page": "Caroline Chisholm School", "text_new": "{{for|the school in Australia|Caroline Chisholm School - Senior Campus}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox school\n| name         = Caroline Chisholm School\n| image        = Caroline_Chisholm_logo.jpg\n| image_size         = 140px\n| coordinates  = {{coord|52.198697|-0.873928|type:edu_region:GB_dim:100|format=dec|display=inline,title}}\n| motto        = \n| established  = 2004\n| closed       =\n| type         = State, all-through Primary and Secondary School, [[Academy (English school)|Academy]]\n| religious_affiliation     =  \n| president    =\n| head_label   = Headteacher\n| head         = .<ref name=bbc25m/>\n| r_head_label =\n| r_head       =\n| chair_label  = Chair of Governors\n| chair        = TBD\n| founder      = [[Northamptonshire County Council]]\n| specialist   =\n| address       = Wooldale Road, [[Wootton, Northamptonshire|Wootton]]\n| city         = [[Northampton]]\n| county       = [[Northamptonshire]]\n| country      = England\n| postcode     = NN4 6TP\n| ofsted       = yes\n| urn          = 137089\n| staff        =\n| enrolment   = ''1634 (2009)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ofsted.gov.uk/inspection-reports/find-inspection-report/provider/ELS/134177 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-09-16 |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024151110/http://www.ofsted.gov.uk/inspection-reports/find-inspection-report/provider/ELS/134177 |archivedate=24 October 2012}}</ref> 1841 (2012)<ref>http://www.ofsted.gov.uk/inspection-reports/find-inspection-report/provider/ELS/137089</ref>\n| gender       = [[Mixed-sex education|Mixed]]\n| lower_age    = 4\n| upper_age    = 18\n| houses       =\n| colours      =\n| publication  =\n| free_label_1 =\n| free_1       =\n| free_label_2 =\n| free_2       =\n| free_label_3 =\n| free_3       =\n| website      = http://www.ccs.northants.sch.uk\n}}\n\n'''Caroline Chisholm School''' is a [[Mixed-sex education|mixed]] [[all-through school]] with [[Academy (English school)|academy status]], in south [[Northampton]], England. It is named after [[Caroline Chisholm]], a 19th-century [[social reformer]].<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/northamptonshire/asop/people/caroline_chisholm.shtml \"Caroline Chisholm 1808 - 1877\"], [[BBC]], January 2004</ref> The [[Principal (school)|principal]] is David James.<ref name=bbc25m/> The school was built in 15 months and cost \u00a325 million.<ref name=bbc25m>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/england/northamptonshire/3630414.stm \"Pupils start at new \u00a325m school\"], [[BBC News]], 6 September 2004</ref> The school added its final year, year 13, in September 2008.<ref name=official>[http://www.ccs.northants.sch.uk/ \"Welcome to Caroline Chisholm School\"], Caroline Chisholm School</ref> In 2005 admission arrangements were changed to give brothers and sisters of children at the school greater priority for places.<ref>[http://www.gnn.gov.uk/Content/Detail.asp?ReleaseID=163559&NewsAreaID=2 \"ADJUDICATOR PUBLISHES DECISION ON PROPOSAL TO VARY THE ADMISSIONS ARRANGEMENTS FOR CAROLINE CHISHOLM SCHOOL, PRESTON HEDGES PRIMARY SCHOOL, WOOTTON PR \"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927191748/http://www.gnn.gov.uk/Content/Detail.asp?ReleaseID=163559&NewsAreaID=2 |date=27 September 2007 }}, Office of The Schools Adjudicator (East Midlands), [[Government News Network]], 15 July 2005</ref>\n\n==Design==\nThe school has 6 blocks, A Block (Music, Drama and PE), B Block (Languages and Humanities), C Block (Maths and English), D Block (Technology and Science), E Block (ICT, Business and Art) and F Block (Primary Phase). It also has a cafeteria, takeaway area, numerous ICT suites, drama studios, gym, art display area, and public meeting rooms.\n\n==Distinctions==\n* This was the first through 4-18 [[state school]] in the [[United Kingdom|UK]].<ref>[http://politics.guardian.co.uk/conservatives/story/0,9061,1493994,00.html?gusrc=rss \"Snap Tory leadership poll impossible\"], Matthew Temple, [[The Guardian]], 27 May 2005</ref>\n* The school was mentioned in the [[House of Lords]] when it was confirmed that this was one of just six schools in England defined as a [[middle school]] that educates year 11 pupils.<ref>[https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200405/ldhansrd/vo050209/text/50209w02.htm \"Middle Schools\"], [[Hansard]], [[House of Lords]], 9 February 2005, Column WA118</ref>\n* [[Secretary of State for Education and Skills|Education Secretary]] [[Ruth Kelly]] visited the school on 17 March 2005.<ref>[http://education.guardian.co.uk/egweekly/story/0,,1573480,00.html \"Ruth Kelly was here\"], Polly Curtis, [[The Guardian]], 20 September 2005</ref><ref>[http://moreresults.factiva.com/results/index/index.aspx?ref=NORHET0020050319e13i00002 \"In a class of its own\"], Northampton Evening Telegraph, 18 March 2005</ref><ref>[http://www.bdp.co.uk/html/news/2005/Minister_Opens_World_Class_BDP_School_122.asp \"Minister Opens \"World Class\" BDP School\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070607195150/http://www.bdp.co.uk/html/news/2005/Minister_Opens_World_Class_BDP_School_122.asp |date=7 June 2007 }}, [[Building Design Partnership]], 23 March 2005</ref>\n\n==Community involvement==\nThe school is in the [[Wooldale Centre for Learning]], a multi-use community facility.<ref name=bbc25m/> Caroline Chisholm has been described as \"unique and ground\nbreaking\" for the way it is linked into the community including offering sports and learning facilities for the whole community.\nKajima Community manage the busy community activities during the evenings and weekends - www.ccs.schoolbookings.co.uk.<ref>[http://www.northamptonshire.gov.uk/NR/rdonlyres/5A6588EB-6A4B-4AED-8417-9E0869FE9132/0/govwin04web.pdf \"Building and Opening a 21st Century School\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928003419/http://www.northamptonshire.gov.uk/NR/rdonlyres/5A6588EB-6A4B-4AED-8417-9E0869FE9132/0/govwin04web.pdf |date=28 September 2007 }}, The Northamptonshire Governor, Winter 2004</ref>\n\n==Academic standards==\n[[Office for Standards in Education|Ofsted's]] report of 17 May 2006 describes the school as: \n{{quote|Caroline Chisholm is a good school with many outstanding features, a view shared by parents and reflected in the school\u2019s self-evaluation. Outstanding features such as the quality and standards in the Foundation Stage, the progress made by pupils with a statement of [[autism spectrum]] disorders, the behaviour and attitudes of all pupils, and the personal development and well-being of pupils make Caroline Chisholm a unique school.}}\n\nIt had 'outstanding' outcome from its Ofsted report in July 2009, while they received a 'good' outcome from their Ofsted report in 2012 due to goku fighting vegeta again in C block. Caroline Chisholm school received 'requires improvement' in their latest Ofsted report in 2018.<ref>{{cite web  |title=Ofsted report 2006  |url=http://www.ofsted.gov.uk/oxedu_providers/full/(urn)/134177  |accessdate=1 September 2008  |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090606232310/http://www.ofsted.gov.uk/oxedu_providers/full/%28urn%29/134177  |archivedate=6 June 2009 }}</ref>\n\n==Catchment area row==\nAlthough the area is next to the large housing development of [[Grange Park, Northamptonshire|Grange Park]], a proposal in January 2010 by Northamptonshire County Council to remove Woodland View Primary School in Grange Park as a feeder school provoked huge protest from Grange Park parents. The alternative schools proposed were Roade School Sports College and [[Abbeyfield School, Northampton|Abbeyfield School]]. (formerly Mereway Secondary School).<ref name =\"C&E20100121\">[http://www.northamptonchron.co.uk/news/Parents39-plan-may-cause-gridlock.5995476.jp Chronicle & Echo, Northampton \"Parents' plan may cause gridlock\" 21 January 2010, accessed 4 March 2010]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.ccs.northants.sch.uk/ Official site]\n\n{{Schools in Northamptonshire}}\n\n[[Category:Academies in Northamptonshire]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2004]]\n[[Category:Primary schools in Northamptonshire]]\n[[Category:Secondary schools in Northamptonshire]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the school in Australia|Caroline Chisholm School - Senior Campus}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox school\n| name         = Caroline Chisholm School\n| image        = Caroline_Chisholm_logo.jpg\n| image_size         = 140px\n| coordinates  = {{coord|52.198697|-0.873928|type:edu_region:GB_dim:100|format=dec|display=inline,title}}\n| motto        = \n| established  = 2004\n| closed       =\n| type         = State, all-through Primary and Secondary School, [[Academy (English school)|Academy]]\n| religious_affiliation     =  \n| president    =\n| head_label   = Headteacher\n| head         = .<ref name=bbc25m/>\n| r_head_label =\n| r_head       =\n| chair_label  = Chair of Governors\n| chair        = TBD\n| founder      = [[Northamptonshire County Council]]\n| specialist   =\n| address       = Wooldale Road, [[Wootton, Northamptonshire|Wootton]]\n| city         = [[Northampton]]\n| county       = [[Northamptonshire]]\n| country      = England\n| postcode     = NN4 6TP\n| ofsted       = yes\n| urn          = 137089\n| staff        =\n| enrolment   = ''1634 (2009)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ofsted.gov.uk/inspection-reports/find-inspection-report/provider/ELS/134177 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-09-16 |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024151110/http://www.ofsted.gov.uk/inspection-reports/find-inspection-report/provider/ELS/134177 |archivedate=24 October 2012}}</ref> 1841 (2012)<ref>http://www.ofsted.gov.uk/inspection-reports/find-inspection-report/provider/ELS/137089</ref>\n| gender       = [[Mixed-sex education|Mixed]]\n| lower_age    = 4\n| upper_age    = 18\n| houses       =\n| colours      =\n| publication  =\n| free_label_